The paper deals with the problem of concept drift in machine learning classifiers, specifically in the context of adversarial activity. This makes it relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), cybersecurity (cs.CR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and data structures (cs.DS). However, given the focus on machine learning and classification, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.CR due to the emphasis on adversarial activity.
